Pre-Game Insights: Both Georgia and Czech Republic are at the bottom of Group F and aim to get off the mark at Euro 2024 when they meet on June 22, 2024.
Georgia scored their first-ever goal at a major tournament in their opening match against Turkey.
The Czech Republic scored the opener in their first Group F fixture against Portugal but eventually lost due to an own goal and a late winner by Portugal.
Key players for Georgia include Georges Mikautadze, who scored Georgia’s first-ever goal at a major tournament, and Khvicha Kvaratskhelia, who is crucial in attack.
Key players for the Czech Republic include Patrik Schick, the top goalscorer in the squad with 19 goals, and Tomas Soucek, an influential midfielder from West Ham United.
The match marks the first encounter between Georgia and Czech Republic in any competition.
Predictions favor the Czech Republic to win with a slight edge due to their experience and attacking quality.
Both teams are expected to score, and the match is anticipated to have over 2.5 goals.
Georgia had 14 shots at goal in their opening match, the most by any debutant since Austria in 2008.
